# Harness runtime state, wherever it lands. The `**/` is load-bearing: a bare
# `.claude/harness/` has a mid-pattern separator, so git anchors it to the repo
# root and misses runtime state written under a subdir (e.g. a test run's
# tests/.claude/harness/, which leaked into the tree before this was widened).
**/.claude/harness/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
.env

# playwright-cli snapshot/console artifacts from local behavioral QA — generated,
# not source; keep them out of the tree (Codex review flagged the churn risk).
.playwright-cli/

# Verbatim vendored OpenAI Symphony reference (Apache-2.0) — local oracle only,
# mirroring the /tmp/symphony-research pattern. Lint-scoped via docs/.harnessignore.
docs/symphony-original/

# Local educational article (beginner walkthrough of the harness + orchestration);
# not a governed repo deliverable — kept local only.
/EDUCATION.md

# Worker runtime (TS, subtree-absorbed from the cc-codex-appserver project).
# Source-only commits: node_modules and tsc build output are generated by
# `npm install` (app-server's `prepare` builds dist/bin.js). Keep them out.
worker-runtime/**/node_modules/
worker-runtime/**/dist/
